      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we recently generated 6.5 billion reads and 1.6 Tb of DNA sequence in order to create a single 3D map of the genome at kilobase resolution (Rao et al., 2014)... Juicer is closely based on the algorithms that we recently developed to analyze and annotate our terabase-scale Hi-C experiments",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly discusses kilobase-resolution Hi-C maps and Juicer's design for such data.",
