    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-domain-boundary-detection/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Contact domains are identified using a dynamic programming algorithm that relies on applying the Arrowhead transformation [Ai,i + d = (M* i,i-d \u2013 M* i,i+d )/(M* i,i-d + M* i,i+d )] to a normalized contact matrix M*",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses the term 'contact domains' rather than 'TADs' (topologically associating domains). While these are functionally equivalent concepts, the paper does not use the acronym TAD.",
