    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/encode-hic-pipeline-execution/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Juicer contains a suite of algorithms that are designed to annotate contact matrices and thus identify features of genome folding. These features include loops, loop anchor motifs, and contact domains. Loops are identified using the HiCCUPS algorithm... Contact domains are identified using a dynamic programming algorithm that relies on applying the Arrowhead transformation... Juicer includes an implementation of Aggregate Peak Analysis (Rao et al., 2014).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes HiCCUPS, Arrowhead, and APA as algorithms/components within Juicer, and notes that 'all feature annotation algorithms in Java as fully-automated, end-to-end tools' were re-implemented. However, the paper does not use the term 'Juicer Tools' as a distinct product name; these are described as integrated components of Juicer itself.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1016-j-cels-2016-07-002",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
