    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hi-c-normalization-and-bias-correction/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A wide array of quality statistics is also calculated, making it possible to assess the success and reliability of a given experiment... Finally, Juicer contains a suite of algorithms that are designed to annotate contact matrices and thus identify features of genome folding. These features include loops, loop anchor motifs, and contact domains.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms normalization enables downstream analysis (domain detection, loop calling) but does not explicitly discuss merging replicates or comparative genomics applications.",
